places.description:
The Ponte 25 de Abril suspension bridge is one of Lisbon’s most notable landmarks as it spans the River Tagus at the narrowest point. The date name remembers the Portuguese Carnation Revolution of 25 April 1974. Crossing the Ponte 25 de Abril bridge makes for a fantastic entrance to Lisbon.

Source: Lisbon Portugal Guide

Let’s talk about groceries. Food shopping and meal prepping not only saves you money, but keeps you on a healthier routine.
. . .
My grocery list consist of:
- Fresh veggies for the week. I usually buy arugula, spinach, broccoli, multicolor bell peppers, butternut squash and/or sweet potato, and avocado
- I don’t buy as many fruits. I get blueberries for my yogurt, and I put grapes in the freezer as a snack or treat. I buy lemon to make hot water with lemon - it is a great way to start your day with a refreshing cleanse.
- I buy a few frozen veggies in case my fresh veggies go bad, and veggie burgers in case I need to add more substance to my meal.
- I always have dried fruits in my pantry. My faves are dried mango and dried apricots. I also really love dried cranberries.
. . .
Also, I’m trying to reduce the amount of plastic I use. I’ve been carrying around a reusable tote bag when I go shopping so I don’t have to use their bags. When I go food shopping I skip putting the veggies in a plastic and instead throw them right in the tote. I use metal utensils when I can and don’t take plastic lids or straws when getting iced drinks. Everything helps!! . . .
What are some of your grocery list musts? Also, if you have any tips or tricks on how to make it easier to reduce, reuse, and recycle, let me know!
